body:
> This is a really odd one. NPE at [ConditionalDependenciesEnabler.java:183](https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/3.24.2/devtools/gradle/gradle-model/src/main/java/io/quarkus/gradle/dependency/ConditionalDependenciesEnabler.java#L183) suggests that
> 
> ```
> 183 // conditionalDepConfiguration.exclude(Map.of(
> 184 //                     "group", rule.getGroup(),
> 185 //                     "module", rule.getModule()))
> ```
> 
> `conditionalDepConfiguration` is null, but that really shouldn't be the case since nowhere in Gradle docs can I find a mention that `project.getConfigurations().detachedConfiguration()` may return null.
> 
> Additionally, I just tried with a fresh project using 3.24.2 and added some exclusions - I can't seem to reproduce the issue. [@fedork](https://github.com/fedork) if you can't supply a reproducer, could you perhaps share your `build.gradle` file?

here is the build file:

```
plugins {
    id 'java'
    id 'groovy'
    id 'io.quarkus'
    id 'jacoco'
}

group = 'com.gappify'
version = '1.0.0-SNAPSHOT'

java {
    sourceCompatibility = JavaVersion.VERSION_17
    targetCompatibility = JavaVersion.VERSION_17
}

repositories {
    mavenCentral()
    mavenLocal()
}

jacoco {
    toolVersion = "0.8.12"
}

configurations.all {
    exclude group: 'commons-logging'
    exclude group: 'org.jctools'
    exclude group: 'jakarta.authentication'
}

dependencies {
    implementation enforcedPlatform("${quarkusPlatformGroupId}:${quarkusPlatformArtifactId}:${quarkusPlatformVersion}")
    implementation 'io.quarkus:quarkus-rest-jackson'
    implementation 'io.quarkus:quarkus-rest'
    implementation 'io.quarkus:quarkus-rest-client'
    implementation 'io.quarkus:quarkus-rest-client-jackson'
    implementation 'io.quarkus:quarkus-qute'
    implementation 'io.quarkus:quarkus-elytron-security:3.2.0.Final'
    implementation 'io.quarkus:quarkus-elytron-security-properties-file:3.2.0.Final'
    implementation 'io.quarkus:quarkus-smallrye-openapi'
    implementation 'io.quarkus:quarkus-smallrye-health'
    implementation 'io.quarkus:quarkus-smallrye-fault-tolerance'
    implementation 'org.eclipse.microprofile.openapi:microprofile-openapi-api:3.1.1'
    implementation 'org.json:json:20231013'

    implementation 'com.google.guava:guava:32.1.2-jre'
    implementation 'org.slf4j:slf4j-api:2.0.9'

    implementation 'org.hibernate:hibernate-validator:8.0.1.Final'
    implementation 'javax.el:javax.el-api:3.0.0'
    implementation 'org.glassfish:javax.el:3.0.0'
    implementation 'commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils:1.9.4'

    // Lombok is used to generate getters, setters, equals, hashCode, toString, etc.
    compileOnly 'org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20'
    annotationProcessor 'org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20'

    // anthropic api
    implementation 'com.anthropic:anthropic-java:2.1.0'

    implementation 'com.opencsv:opencsv:5.8'

    // Apache Commons Math for statistical calculations
    implementation 'org.apache.commons:commons-math3:3.+'

    // Test dependencies
    testCompileOnly 'org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20'
    testAnnotationProcessor 'org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20'
    testImplementation 'io.quarkus:quarkus-junit5'
    testImplementation 'io.rest-assured:rest-assured'

    // Spock
    testImplementation 'org.spockframework:spock-core:2.3-groovy-4.0'
    testImplementation 'net.bytebuddy:byte-buddy:1.14.9'
}

// Configure your test tasks to use JUnit Platform
tasks.withType(Test).configureEach {
    useJUnitPlatform()
}

test {
    systemProperty "java.util.logging.manager", "org.jboss.logmanager.LogManager"
    finalizedBy jacocoTestReport
}

compileJava {
    options.encoding = 'UTF-8'
    options.compilerArgs << '-parameters'
}

compileTestJava {
    options.encoding = 'UTF-8'
}

jacocoTestReport {
    dependsOn test
    reports {
        xml.required = true   // Enable XML report (for Bitbucket pipeline check)
        html.required = true  // Enable HTML report (for local debugging)
        csv.required = false
    }
}

```

@fedork thanks, this is helpful. Now I can reproduce your issue and I understand why this happened.
For anybody interested, the issue was writing a null value into an immutable map value on L185.

I'm preparing a PR to fix this.
